caption: Best sushi in the area. Great selection of Japanese food products.
(Translated by Google) I always buy Japanese food 😊  (Original) いつも日本食買ってます😊

This place is my favorite place.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to that place. when  I want to go to a good meal, this place comes instantly to my mind.  Great and   food and a large list of dishes.helpful staff, and great ambience. Not less important, the bill is good. I recommend this spot with pleasure.
Oyishi-des! Very friendly staff and lots of great food.
Love the duo that runs this spot. They are very sweet. Great selection of products for a small shop and amazing sushi/sashimi/nigiri. Parallels any expensive sushi spot especially in take out land.
Local Japanese foods market with delicious take out sushi, and hard to find produce.

The most authentic sushi in all of Bethesda. Hinata is a wonderful, hidden gem of a spot for real, true-to-cuisine Japanese food and grocery.  I actually stumbled upon this place walking my dog and it soon became a routine stop for us when we lived in downtown Bethesda. I would get their sushi specials along with some of my favorite Japanese grocery items reminiscent of my time working in Japan. The proprietor is very kind and friendly. She would take my order and would bring it outside to me as my dog and I waited for the food. Highly recommend this place to anyone who loves sushi or any Japanese food items. Five stars all-around!
Doesn't make sense how good the sushi is. Having been to Japan, all I can say is ... Excellent!
You have to call an order ahead at least 45 min. Hands down best sushi in Bethesda! I wouldn't and don't go anywhere else for my sushi cravings.
Really nice place, a good variety of japanese drinks, frozen food and treats. You can also carry out the day before or same day but an hour and a half before. Will come back soon

This place is an amazing hidden gem in Bethesda. Haven’t tried their sushi yet (have heard many great things about it) but their convenient store is amazing. They have almost everything you will ever need for Japanese food (both cooking materials and snack). Everything they sell are really authentic and not pricey at all. A must go for Japanese food lovers.
Great place for all of your specialty Japanese goods, some fresh veggies, sushi, etc

This is such a special Bethesda institution!  The staff is so kind and welcoming. The selection of goods is amazing, and almost everything is affordable. The sushi is delicious!  It feels a bit as if we've visited Japan for a few minutes when we're there. We visit frequently and have never had a bad experience. Many Japanese (and other Asian) people shop there, which is the true test of authenticity and quality. Hinata gets an A plus from us.
I just enjoyed their dishes. I always get excellent service there. The place is clean and the workers are always very welcoming. I highly recommend this place.

This is probably one of a handful of local "real" japanese owned and run sushi spots in the entire region. This kind of quaint small cramped store with a sushi counter in the back is an amazing small gem in the community. The only thing it can be compared to are shops on the west coast and NYC.  Definitely worth a visit if you want a taste of what this food is supposed to taste like.

The sushi is reasonably priced and delicious. During the pandemic, they've got a bottle of hand sanitizer and some disposable gloves at the door. I'm new to the Bethesda area, and I've definitely found my sushi place!

(Translated by Google) I will change the evaluation. I've bought expired expirations twice over the past few times. I was inadvertent when my friend told me that I had to pay attention to the expiration date when I bought it here. Unfortunately it was Calpis. My little girl says it's a strange taste, so when you bring a cup to your mouth it smells musty! ! The contents were completely moldy. I just opened the seal but threw it all away. In this situation of hesitation to go out, going to the hospital is difficult. I just hope my daughter will not get hungry.  (Original) 評価変えます。 ここ数回、２度にわたって賞味期限切れを購入してしまいました。 お友達からここで買う時はしっかり賞味期限を注意しないとダメと言われていたのにうっかりでした。運の悪いことにそれがカルピスでした。幼い娘がママ変な味と言うので口元にカップを持ってくるとカビ臭い！！完全に中身がカビていました。 封を開けたばかりでしたが全部捨てました。外出にためらうこの状況下、病院行くのも一苦労です。娘がお腹崩さないのを願うばかりです。
Lots of groceries and sushi
This spot is worth a visit. They serve big portions for affordable prices. Always well organized and with great mood. Highly recommended.
Small but good variety of grocery
Lovely little spot. Great and well priced sushi.
I just went to the grocery. I will try sushi next time. There are a lot of Japanese snakes and frozen food.  The staff is friendly.  Small place but i still can have what I need
Great spot for sushi and Japanese groceries. Call ahead though, they get busy and will provide super slow service if not equipped.
Ordered the rainbow roll, spicy tuna, and eel. All were delicious.
Low profile Japanese grocery that also makes delicious sushi with a great selection of fishes

What a hidden jem! Great sushi and a ton of Japanese grocery items. The owners are super friendly and happy to answer any questions you might have about their products (offer recommendations). Most of their items also have English translations on the back (including nutritional information) which is super helpful.
Amazing atmosphere and super welcoming service. The food was crisp and delicious. Will surely recommend this place to anyone. Convenient rates and large meals. Great job.
Excellent
I always like coming here for when I need any type of Japanese snacks.
The owners were really friendly and the place was pretty cozy. Reminded me of life back home!
So adorable and unique Japanese store and eating place. It is small but packed with Japanese snacks and other products. it feels like real Japanese convenient store in japan. suchi is good too.
Quantity was little small, but quality was better than what I anticipated.
Tiny but cute.Authentic Japanese convenient store. Must to visit!🇯🇵
Very good
Great tea and fresh sushi. Small but great selection of Japanese goods. Great Mom and Pop type of place. I appreciated the classical music in the background. Good choice!
Cute, authentic Japanese grocery, helpful staff, delicious sushi with a few tables for eating inside and out.

(Translated by Google) Kishimen, natto, Anpanman senbei, dango --all the good stuff you ’re missing from Japan!  (Original) Kishimen, natto, Anpanman senbei, dango - all the good stuff you’re missing from Japan!
The sushi is always great. The owner is the sweetest lady! My favorite place to grab snacks and tea when I'm visiting the area
Excellent
A hole in the wall on st elm. Not many know it's there but being able to get specialty Asian ingredients, a quick, light lunch, and the quiet space are perfect for midday breaks.

Nice little Japanese store with a wide variety of items we miss from Japan.  It's a small store, but there is a lot packed in there.  We only had time to grab a couple of pieces of nigiri sushi but they were good. It's the States so not super fresh, but still way better then the funky stuff you get at random "hibachi" restaurants in NoVa.  We walked from our hotel but noticed a public parking garage right down the street from the store.
Friendly staffs, great sushi, lots of Japanese groceries, vegetables from Suzuki farm. Love this store.

I stopped by this past Saturday to order sushi to go. Good prices for sushi.  Order a California roll with imitation crab--the real crabmeat was a little bland.   It was fairly busy with patrons buying groceries and such.  It only took 15 minutes to complete my order.  Parking is a premium around 2pm.  Someone came in assuming a large order they phoned in was ready.  Word to the wise: Call ahead and confirm your order is ready.
Love the sushi here. Always fresh and tasty. Fair price for the food and good collection of Asian grocery in such a small space.
Fish is very  very fresh! Portions are small and pricey
A quaint little store with many options! The staff are all very nice! A lot of options for a smaller store.
Very nice employees, good food as well.
Surprisingly delicious. Amazing assortment of Asian products.

Nice little store for fresh sushi and various Japanese grocery items. I wish they had more produce and meat/seafood items but they have a lot of snacks, cooking stuff, and non perishable food, as well as some Frozen stuff. It's a great neighborhood Japanese market! The people that work there are very nice too
The sushi is so good!
Amazing sushi!! Don't let this gem slip past.
Love this little shop! The lady at the register is super nice!
Very friendly! Eat and shop in one single place! Even the daily specials are made to order! My new sushi spot!!! We will definitely be back!

Fun shop for kids obsessed with Japanese snacks (my daughter) and adults looking for good selection of quality Japanese staple ingredients. Staff is exceptionally helpful. And, delicious sushi is best bargain in town!

Good sushi and great to be able to get asian food without having to drive.  I come here pretty often to pick up things i need but don't have time to drive out to H-mart for.  Its great for Japanese stuff like Kombu.  I often buy udon noodles and kombu/dashi to make a quick udon at home.  It's WAY too small though.  Only one person fits in an aisle and if people are in all 3 aisles you can't really get in or out of the place.

The japanese grocery selection alone is why I come here! And it's just a little bit closer and cheaper than Maruichi for me. My only complaint is that they need a bigger location; can't have more than one person in the aisle when you're looking through everything.

This is the only place near the Bethesda metro to carry Asian products. Yes, you can drive 20 minutes to get to H-mart or Great Wall, but you can also walk 10 minutes or drive for a few to get the Hinata, which would carry most Asian products you would need to make Japanese or Chinese dishes. Because the store is small, don't expect them to have everything, just everything that the nearby Safeway and Trader Joe's don't carry.
"Hidden gem" of Bethesda - great selection of Japanese groceries and drinks!
Great sushi, good selection of Japanese products, and such a friendly owner!

Love this place. Came here with a Japanese colleague who works in Bethesda but had never heard about it. They were ecstatic at finding some of the things on the shelves that they have difficulty finding anywhere. I love the sushi specials for lunch and have ordered take out for a party and it was amazing.
Nice market that also offers sushi take out.
Really nice place. Highly recommend
A nice Asian grocery with sushi served at the back of the store. It's nice as a lunch option in Bethesda.
Killer sushi lunch special! Not quite filling enough on its own though.
Very nice market that also happens to make good and inexpensive Japanese food. The owners and staff are very friendly.

The sushi/sashimi is very good and very authentic. It's a wonderful little "tucked away" place, that's always fun to drop by if you're looking for some good quality sushi. The staff is friendly, and there are a wide array of Japanese foodstuffs which can be perused and purchased.  Highly recommend the chirashi sushi.

The sushi here is worth the price, and it is the best deal I have found in the DC area (along with Kotobuki). Everything was good enough, and I liked the noisy and happy conversations between Japanese families.  This is a very casual local place to buy inexpensive sushi, unusual japanese products, and enjoy some cultural differences without spending too much. Highly recommended, but don't expect fast service, gourmet quality or atmosphere. If you want a fancier option while still keeping prices low, try Kotobuki.
